                <property name="text">
                 <string>PyClef was born from a passion for both music and technology.
It was created with the goal of simplifying the reading and analysis of musical scores by combining computational intelligence with music theory in a modern, accessible, and efficient tool.

The idea emerged from the need to transform how musicians and students interact with digital sheet musi, making the process more intuitive, faster, and increasingly automated.

Developed by Vinícius Fernandes, PyClef represents the convergence of artistic creativity and technological innovation.</string>
